# Legacy WP media URLs (`/wp-content/uploads/*`) intentionally not
# redirected. The original Yoast intent was to map them to `/img/:splat`,
# but Astro hashes every asset into `dist/_astro/` so no equivalent path
# exists. Sending them to `/` (the previous rule) produced a soft-404
# for Google Images: the image URL resolved to an HTML page, which
# Google then dropped from the index anyway. Letting them 404 cleanly
# is the same outcome with honest signal; Google Images drops the
# listing within ~30 days either way.
